nto dangerous germs and bioweapons in the name of biodefense, and further, bolstered the U.S. rationale for increased interference in the disease control decisions of global south nations. Bio-Imperialism is a sobering look at how the war on terror impacted the world in ways that we are only just starting to grapple with.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aBiological warfarezUnited States. 0aBioterrorismzUnited States. 0aNational securityzUnited States. 0aRacismxPolitical aspectszUnited States. 7aHISTORY / General.2bisacsh  aWar on Terror, War Politics, Bioterrorism, Science, Bioscience, National Security, Public Health, Third World mortality, Military Studies, Politics, Women's Studies, Science Studies, Health, Health Policy, Medical Studies, Disease, Imperialism, Terrorism, Government, Mass Media, Communities.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2020 Englishz978311070473008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2020z9783110704525oZDB-23-DEG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073913840uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/978197881481340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781978814813423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781978814813/original  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070473-0  EBOOK PACKAGE History 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-073913-8  Rutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL